* Exclude top N finishers by sex from subsequent age-group awards
*
* Purpose:          Marks top N finishers of a specific sex as excluded,
*                   so they don't appear again in age-group results.
*                   Called automatically by @Overall.rsm after listing overall winners.
*
* Param 1 (%1):     Number of runners to exclude (e.g., 3).
* Param 2 (%2):     Sex label (FEMALE or MALE) -- unused but passed for consistency.
* Param 3 (%3):     Sex code for selection (F or M).
*
* Example:          EXCLUDE.RSM 3 FEMALE F
*
No Page Numbers
No Column Headers
Select              SEX
=                   %3
Exclude             %1
event               %awards_event%
